\ running? ( pid -- bool ) — non-blocking liveness via waitpid(WNOHANG).
\ true while the child runs; false once it has exited (reaping it).

variable p

\ a long sleeper is alive
"sleep 60" run to p
p :pid @ running? .  cr          \ 1

\ ... and not alive once stopped (stop SIGKILLs and reaps it)
p :pid @ stop drop
p :pid @ running? .  cr          \ 0

\ a process already reaped by wait is likewise not running
[ "true" ] start-process to p
p :pid @ wait drop
p :pid @ running? .  cr          \ 0

\ error: pid must be a number
"x" running?
